D.N.C. Shop Talk

Your name has been floated as someone who could run for D.N.C. chair. Are y=
ou interested?

I think that the chair of the D.N.C. is a dream job. Whoever gets it would =
and should have a hell of a lot of fun doing it, because there=E2=80=99s so=
 much work to be done, and there=E2=80=99s so much promise with what everyo=
ne could collectively accomplish under the right leader. I=E2=80=99m defini=
tely making phone calls and exploring it, but there are folks who are a lot=
 cooler than me who also have had their name thrown in the mix. So I=E2=80=
=99m not looking at this from the vantage point of personal ambition.

I just sincerely want to be a part of the effort to help, not to necessaril=
y resist=E2=80=94although we should stand up to what this Trump administrat=
ion is doing=E2=80=94but to be a part of the story of the rebirth of the De=
mocratic Party, where we can not just
win elections intermittently, but actually hold on to political power long =
enough to make changes that we know need to actually happen.

You represent a generational change. Is that something you would lean into?

This clearly has to be a moment to begin changing. You could talk about D.N=
=2EC. chair, you could talk about any o=
f these other machinations over the co=
urse of the next 18 months, but the real change is finding those great cand=
idates for the midterm elections in 2026, and getting behind the right pres=
idential candidate, and making sure that=E2=80=99s done through a fair, ope=
n primary process. That=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s going to build our party.

How would you counter the argument being made that Democrats don=E2=80=99t =
want anyone who=E2=80=99s lost an election to run the party?

You learn an incredible amount from losing elections. Many would argue I sh=
ould have never won my first election; it was a district that Donald Trump =
won by 11
points. It=E2=80=99s a district now that Trump just won by over 40 points. =
So, we=E2=80=99re basically looking at incredibly harsh terrain for a Democ=
rat. I=E2=80=99m proud of the fights I engaged in. I=E2=80=99m proud of the=
 hard stances I=E2=80=99ve taken. I=E2=80=99ve made sacrifices for my value=
s, and I=E2=80=99ve got the scars to prove it.

My hope is that I can continue in some way to support the party and help us=
 win elections. And there are a lot of different ways that can come in, but=
 I don=E2=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s a good idea for our party to say, If yo=
u=E2=80=99ve ever lost an election, you have no place. In that case, there =
would have been no place for Bill Clinton or Barack Obama, both of whom los=
t congressional races.

