x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Like virtually ever=
y other ambitious, somewhat underemployed former Democratic pol with a pres=
cription for how to fix the party, ex-congressman <b>Max Rose </b>has his e=
yes on the D.N.C. chairmanship. Rose, 37, would certainly bring <i>generati=
onal</i> change. A decorated Afghanistan veteran, Rose surfed the blue wave=
