          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><b>Your name has be=
en floated as someone who could run for D.N.C. chair. Are you interested?</=
b><br/><br/>I think that the chair of the D.N.C. is a dream job. Whoever ge=
ts it would and should have a hell of a lot of fun doing it, because there=
=E2=80=99s so much work to be done, and there=E2=80=99s so much promise wit=
h what everyone could collectively accomplish under the right leader. I=E2=
=80=99m definitely making phone calls and exploring it, but there are folks=
 who are a lot cooler than me who also have had their name thrown in the mi=
x. So I=E2=80=99m not looking at this from the vantage point of personal am=
bition. <br/><br/>I just sincerely want to be a part of the effort to help,=
 not to necessarily resist=E2=80=94although we should stand up to what this=
 Trump administration is doing=E2=80=94but to be a part of the story of the=
 rebirth of the Democratic Party, where we can not just
win elections intermittently, but actually hold on to political power long =
enough to make changes that we know need to actually happen.<br/><br/><b>Yo=
u represent a generational change. Is that something you would lean into?</=
b><br/><br/>This <i>clearly</i> has to be a moment to begin changing. You c=
ould talk about D.N.C. chair, you could talk about any of these other machi=
nations over the course of the next 18 months, but the real change is findi=
ng those great candidates for the midterm elections in 2026, and getting be=
hind the right presidential candidate, and making sure that=E2=80=99s done =
through a fair, open primary process. That=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s going t=
o build our party. <br/><br/><b>How would you counter the argument being ma=
de that Democrats don=E2=80=99t want anyone who=E2=80=99s lost an election =
to run the party?</b><br/><br/>You learn an incredible amount from losing e=
lections. Many would argue I should have never won my first election; it wa=
s a district that Donald Trump won by 11
points. It=E2=80=99s a district <i>now</i> that Trump just won by over 40 p=
oints. So, we=E2=80=99re basically looking at incredibly harsh terrain for =
a Democrat. I=E2=80=99m proud of the fights I engaged in. I=E2=80=99m proud=
 of the hard stances I=E2=80=99ve taken. I=E2=80=99ve made sacrifices for m=
y values, and I=E2=80=99ve got the scars to prove it. <br/><br/>My hope is =
that I can continue in some way to support the party and help us win electi=
ons. And there are a lot of different ways that can come in, but I don=E2=
=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s a good idea for our party to say, <i>If you=E2=
=80=99ve ever lost an election, you have no place</i>. In that case, there =
would have been no place for <b>Bill Clinton </b>or <b>Barack Obama</b>, bo=
th of whom lost congressional races. <br/></td>
